System of corporate law, main principles, main institutes, legal regulations of different corporate forms in Estonia.
System and principles of law of obligations. Sources of obligations. Signing contracts. Content of obligation. Quittance. Breach of obligations. System and use of remedies. Basics of indemnification. Ending obligations. Ancillary obligations. Transfer of requirements and obligations. Multeity of people. Third parties in obligations. Different forms of contract.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide learners with understanding of the main principles of business law and law of obligations, and the main types of contracts concerning the specialities studied by students.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows business code; 2) knows main institutes of law of obligations; 3) knows main principles of law of obligations; 4) knows fundamental terms of the main types of contracts concerning the specialities studied by students; 5) knows the connections of general and special parts of the law of obligations and the specifics of adjustment; 6) can apply his knowledge when disputing the law of obligations, and analyze the more important business contracts.
